    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0d893cea_e600ab0d",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 461,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-08T16:10:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "1. You should really call sigaltstack to clear the alternate stack (or restore the previous one) before calling munmap, because the thread’s still running at this point and the configured sigaltstack becomes garbage after calling munmap.\n\n2. The destructor will still run even on threads that never called InitializeSignalStack. stack_mem will be nullptr in that case, and this will attempt to munmap kStackAllocSize bytes starting at address 0. You must null-check stack_mem in the destructor function.",
      "revId": "361dc6356c54c36f8395aafcb189d69783a8c431",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e58ac7b8_796096fb",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 470,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-08T16:10:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I’d prefer to only have to log this once, by wrapping the PLOG(ERROR) up into the initializer along with pthread_key_create.",
      "revId": "361dc6356c54c36f8395aafcb189d69783a8c431",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b54ce706_b0eee6a6",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 471,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-08T16:10:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This fires the ScopedMmap destructor, destroying the allocated region, but leaves the sigaltstack configured.\n\nMight be better to do pthread_key_create before sigaltstack. Maybe even before mmap.",
      "revId": "361dc6356c54c36f8395aafcb189d69783a8c431",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
